# Book Bans in the United States 2021-2022

### Description
To investigate the uptick in book banning across the United States, this Plotly/Dash visualization tool will allow you to easily examine book ban metrics with state education scores, school demographics and funding, as well as locating public libraries across the US.

### Datasets Used
1. Banned Books dataset from Center for Data Innovation (https://datainnovation.org/2022/07/tracking-banned-books/)
2. US Census dataset from Kaggle (https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/muonneutrino/us-census-demographic-data?select=acs2015_county_data.csv)
3. Public Library dataset from Kaggle (https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/imls/public-libraries)
4. US states geoJson file from GitHub (https://github.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/blob/master/data/geojson/us-states.json)
5. State code and name dictionary from Kaggle (https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/jonbown/state-code)


### Instructions
1. Clone repository
2. Open repository in your terminal
3. Execute "jupyter-lab" command
4. Open jupyter notebook in jupyter-lab
5. Run entire kernal
6. Open link: http://127.0.0.1:8050/
7. Explore the dashboard
